===============================
| Object-Oriented Programming |
===============================
👉 Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) is a programming paradigm that uses classes and objects to organize code, allowing data and methods to be 
   bundled together for better modularity, reusability, and maintainability.
  👉 OOP stands for Object-Oriented Programming.
  👉 Java is an object-oriented language.
  👉 OOP is based on Classes and Objects.
  👉 Objects contain data and methods.
  👉 OOP improves code reusability and maintainability.
  👉 The six main concepts are Class, Object, Encapsulation, Inheritance, Polymorphism, and Abstraction.

Class in Java
--------------
👉 A Class is a blueprint or template used to create objects. It defines the properties (fields) and behaviors (methods) that the objects will have.
    Blueprint → House
    Class → Object

Car Class
      │
      ├──────────────┐
      │              │
      ▼              ▼
Car1            Car2
Red             Blue
BMW             Audi

Car Class → Blueprint
Car1, Car2 → Objects

---------------------------------------------
class ClassName {
    // Fields (Variables)
    // Constructors
    // Methods
}
---------------------------------------------
class Student {            // Student Class
    String name;           // instance variable
    int age;              // instance variable
    void study() {        // Method
        System.out.println("Student is studying");
    }
}


Class Components
------------------
Class
│
├── Fields
│
├── Constructors
│
├── Methods
│
├── Nested Classes
│
└── Static Members

👉 Fields (Instance Variables) -> Fields are variables declared inside a class that store the data of an object.

class Student {
    String name;
    int age;
    double marks;
}

👉 Methods -> Methods define the behavior or actions that an object can perform.

class Student {
    void study() {
        System.out.println("Studying...");
    }
    void sleep() {
        System.out.println("Sleeping...");
    }
}

👉 Constructors -> A constructor is a special method used to initialize objects.

class Student {
    Student() {
    }
}

